
# Dewen Liu

**Email:** dwliu23@m.fudan.edu.cn  

### Biography

I am an undergraduate student majoring in Intelligent Science and Technology at the College of Intelligent Robotics and Advanced Manufacturing, Fudan University. Maintaining a GPA of 3.87/4.0 and ranking 2nd in my cohort, I have built a rigorous foundation in computer science and artificial intelligence. I am currently preparing to pursue a direct Ph.D. program starting in 2027.

My primary research focuses on Large Language Model (LLM)-based Multi-Agent Systems (MAS). I am particularly dedicated to establishing scientific evaluation frameworks and exploring the mechanisms of emergence regulation under system scaling. To optimize organizational structures and agent heterogeneity, I actively integrate algorithms such as Reinforcement Learning (RL) and Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) into training frameworks. Beyond software-level MAS, I am also deeply interested in embodied intelligence, actively exploring how these cognitive architectures can be deployed in physical systems like bipedal robotics to achieve robust, real-world interactions.

